                                <h2 class="dark-text">Help Center shop page (app proxy) <a href="#top">#back to top</a><hr></h2>
                            </div>
                            <!-- end col -->
                        </div>
                        <!-- end row -->
                        <p>By default, Atlas app displays your help center main page at "YourShopifyDomain.com/apps/help-center", Shopify provides a way for you to change this URL. Hers is how you could achieve that:</p>
                        <ul style="list-style-type: none;">
                            <li><h3>1. Go to your Shopify Admin Area and click > "Apps".</h3></li>
                            <li><h3>2. On the "Installed apps" section, find "Atlas - Help Center" app and click "About".</h3></li>
                            <li><img class="presentation_image contain-image" src="/docs/images/upload/app_details.jpg" alt="" /></li>
                            <li><h3>3. Scroll down > App proxy > Customize URL, then save. That's it.</h3></li>
                        </ul>
                        <hr>
