                                <h2 class="dark-text">The Launcher <a href="#top">#back to top</a><hr></h2>
                            </div>
                            <!-- end col -->
                        </div>
                        <!-- end row -->
                        <p>Atlas Launcher is a messenger like widget that shows within all your store pages.</p>
                        <h3>Basic use</h3>
                        <p>Activate/Deactivate the launcher, change colors, icons and add custom CSS from within the app settings admin page.</p>
                        <h3>Advanced use</h3>
                        <p>If youâ€™d like the Launcher to open from a specific button, link, or element in your website, you can create a custom trigger-element. For example, you can trigger the Launcher to open when a customer clicks on a "Shiping" button and also load that category content.</p>
                        <p>The supported Launcher actions are: open at home, open at a specific category, open at a specific article, and close. Below you can find a few examples.</p>
                        <code>&lt;a class="atlas-launcher-trigger" data-nav-type="close"&gt;Close launcher&lt;/a&gt;</code><br>
                        <code>&lt;a class="atlas-launcher-trigger" data-nav-type="home"&gt;Open launcher home&lt;/a&gt;</code><br>
                        <code>&lt;a class="atlas-launcher-trigger" data-nav-type="category" data-slug="CATEGORY-SLUG"&gt;Open launcher at category&lt;/a&gt;</code><br>
                        <code>&lt;a class="atlas-launcher-trigger" data-nav-type="article" data-slug="ARTICLE-SLUG"&gt;Open launcher at article&lt;/a&gt;</code><br>
                        <p><b>Note!</b> You can obtain your category and article slugs when you create or edit a category or an article.</p>
                        <hr>
